               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799" evidence="lettering" cert="low"/>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     The manuscript was sent from Ethiopia in <date>1868</date> by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS11364Knight">Knight</persName>;
                     it thus  either belongs to the manuscripts looted by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName>
                     expedition in <date>1868</date> from the church of <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿAlam</placeName>
                     or was acquired by a member of the expedition between <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5534Sanafe">Sanʿāfe</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC4547Maqdal">Maqdalā</placeName>. 
                     It was purchased by the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0312BDL">Bodleian Library</placeName> in <date>1883</date>.
                  </provenance>
               </history>
               
